  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>the multimodal analgesic effect of pregabalin, and of pregabalin with dexamethasone</measure>
    <time_frame>Assessment was performed during the first 72 hour following emergence from general anesthesia, subdivided into 5 time periods; on arrival of patient to the PACU, 1-6 hour, 6-24 hour, 24-48 hour and 48-72 hour</time_frame>
    <description>Primary Outcome is to investigate the multimodal analgesic effect of pregabalin, and of pregabalin with dexamethasone, in patients receiving a patient-controlled analgeisa with fentanyl, on fentanyl consumption (primary end point), pain scores and side effects in patients scheduled for lumbar spinal surgery.</description>
